 
<p>

The giant accounting company EY offered to split up into an accounting
company and a consulting company.  That split would limit opportunities and
temptation for corruption.  The US <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/apr/11/ey-plan-to-break-up-consultancy-and-audit-divisions-blocked-by-us-office">objected to a detail of the plan</a>.
<p>
I wonder what the objection was.  Was the US protecting corruption?
Or was EY's plan designed to play a fast one?

 